<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Minesweeper is a single-player puzzle video game. The objective of the game is to clear a rectangular board containing hidden " mines
        " or bombs without detonating any of them, with help from clues about the number of neighboring mines in each field. The game originates from the 1960s, and it has been written for many computing platforms in use today. It has many variations and offshoots.">
    <title>Minesweeper</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://pro.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.10.0/css/all.css" integrity="sha384-AYmEC3Yw5cVb3ZcuHtOA93w35dYTsvhLPVnYs9eStHfGJvOvKxVfELGroGkvsg+p" crossorigin="anonymous" />
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-KyZXEAg3QhqLMpG8r+8fhAXLRk2vvoC2f3B09zVXn8CA5QIVfZOJ3BCsw2P0p/We" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css">

    <!-- CSS only -->
</head>

<body>

    <!-- JavaScript Bundle with Popper -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-U1DAWAznBHeqEIlVSCgzq+c9gqGAJn5c/t99JyeKa9xxaYpSvHU5awsuZVVFIhvj" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

    <!-- heading -->
    <div class="heading">
        <h1>Mineswee<img class="heading-img" src="/images/flag.png" alt="" />er</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- score -->
    <div class="score">
        <div class="highest-score">
            <div class="score-head">
                Highest Score
            </div>
            <div class="score-number">
                000
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="last-score">
            <div class="score-head">
                Last Score
            </div>
            <div class="score-number">
                000
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- levels -->
    <div class="levels">
        <div class="easy">Easy</div>
        <div class="medium">Medium</div>
        <div class="hard">Hard</div>
    </div>

    <!-- info -->

    <div class="info" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal">
        <i class="fas fa-info-circle fa-lg"></i>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Modal -->
    <div class="modal fade" id="exampleModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
          <div class="modal-content rules">
            <div class="modal-header">
              <h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLabel">Rules</h5>
              <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                Minesweeper rules are very simple. The board is divided into cells, with mines randomly distributed. To win, you need to open all the cells. The number on a cell shows the number of mines adjacent to it. Using this information, you can determine cells that are safe, and cells that contain mines. Cells suspected of being mines can be marked with a flag using the right mouse button.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
  
    
    <!-- footer -->
    <footer class="fixed-bottom">
        <div class="footer">Made with ❣️</div>
    </footer>
</body>

</html>